predict:
WITH diagnosis_outcomes AS (
    SELECT 
        d.diagnosisname,
        COUNT(DISTINCT p.patientunitstayid) AS total_patients,
        SUM(CASE WHEN p.hospitaldischargestatus = 'expired' 
                 AND (julianday(p.hospitaldischargetime) - julianday(d.diagnosistime)) <= 365*2
            THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS died_within_two_years
    FROM 
        diagnosis d
    JOIN 
        patient p ON d.patientunitstayid = p.patientunitstayid
    GROUP BY 
        d.diagnosisname
    HAVING 
        total_patients >= 10 -- Minimum sample size for statistical relevance
),
mortality_rates AS (
    SELECT
        diagnosisname,
        total_patients,
        died_within_two_years,
        CAST(died_within_two_years AS FLOAT) / total_patients AS mortality_rate
    FROM
        diagnosis_outcomes
)
SELECT 
    diagnosisname,
    total_patients,
    died_within_two_years,
    ROUND(mortality_rate * 100, 2) AS mortality_rate_percent
FROM 
    mortality_rates
ORDER BY 
    mortality_rate DESC
LIMIT 3;

input: give me the top five diagnoses that have the highest one
predict:
SELECT 
    d.diagnosisname,
    COUNT(DISTINCT d.patientunitstayid) AS total_patients,
    SUM(CASE WHEN p.hospitaldischargestatus = 'expired' 
             AND (JULIANDAY(p.hospitaldischargetime) - JULIANDAY(d.diagnosistime)) <= 365 
             THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS deaths_within_year,
    ROUND(100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN p.hospitaldischargestatus = 'expired' 
                          AND (JULIANDAY(p.hospitaldischargetime) - JULIANDAY(d.diagnosistime)) <= 365 
                          THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(DISTINCT d.patientunitstayid), 2) AS mortality_rate_percent
FROM 
    diagnosis d
JOIN 
    patient p ON d.patientunitstayid = p.patientunitstayid
GROUP BY 
    d.diagnosisname
HAVING 
    COUNT(DISTINCT d.patientunitstayid) >= 10 -- Minimum sample size for statistical significance
ORDER BY 
    mortality_rate_percent DESC
LIMIT 5;

input: what is the minimum total cost of a hospital, including a procedure called bronchodilator - leukotriene
predict:
SELECT p.hospitalid, SUM(c.cost) as total_cost
FROM patient p
JOIN cost c ON p.uniquepid = c.uniquepid AND p.patienthealthsystemstayid = c.patienthealthsystemstayid
WHERE p.hospitalid IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT p2.hospitalid
    FROM patient p2
    JOIN treatment t ON p2.patientunitstayid = t.patientunitstayid
    WHERE LOWER(t.treatmentname) = 'bronchodilator - leukotriene receptor antagonists'
    UNION
    SELECT DISTINCT p3.hospitalid
    FROM patient p3
    JOIN medication m ON p3.patientunitstayid = m.patientunitstayid
    WHERE LOWER(m.drugname) = 'bronchodilator - leukotriene receptor antagonists'
)
GROUP BY p.hospitalid
ORDER BY total_cost ASC
LIMIT 1;

WITH cancer_diagnoses AS (
    SELECT 
        patientunitstayid,
        diagnosistime,
        DATE(diagnosistime, 'start of month') AS diagnosis_month
    FROM diagnosis
    WHERE 
        diagnosisname LIKE '%esophageal ca%'
        AND diagnosistime >= '2104-12-31 23:59:00'
)

    lab.labname,
    COUNT(*) AS frequency
FROM lab
JOIN cancer_diagnoses ON lab.patientunitstayid = cancer_diagnoses.patientunitstayid
WHERE 
    DATE(lab.labresulttime, 'start of month') = cancer_diagnoses.diagnosis_month
    AND lab.labresulttime >= cancer_diagnoses.diagnosistime
GROUP BY lab.labname
ORDER BY frequency DESC
LIMIT 5;
